    %h3
      What is Signal?
    %p
      %a{:href => "Signal_Blue_Icon.png", :target => "_blank"}
        %img{:src => "/images/presentations/signal.png"}
    %ul
      %li Signal is a secure communication platform from Open Whisper Systems
      %li Provides a secure, easy to use alternative to calling, texting, and video chat
      %li Successor to RedPhone and TextSecure
      %li Uses data connection instead of phone network
      %li Signal seamlessly integrates with phone/SMS for the rest of your contacts
  %section
    %h3
      How do I use Signal to communicate?
    %img{:src => "/images/presentations/signal-conversation-list.png"}
  %section
    %h3
      How do I use Signal to communicate?
    %ul
      %li Instead of calling your contact, try a Signal voice call
      %li Instead of sending a text message, send it with Signal. Group chat is supported as well
      %li You can also video chat (no FaceTime, Allo)
      %li You can still share pictures and other media
      %li For contacts without Signal, fallback to the phone network
      %li Invite your friends to use Signal too!
  %section
    %h3
      How does Signal protect my communications?
    %ul
      %li Provides end-to-end encryption and authentication for text, audio, and video chat
      %li Based on trusted crypto primitives like Curve25519, AES-256, and HMAC-SHA256
      %li Bunch of other cool privacy features like disappearing messages, key change alerts and verification, and local message db encryption
      %li Leaves less metadata than using the phone network or other communication apps
  %section
    %h3
      Where can I get Signal?
    %ul
      %li Signal is available for mobile in the Google Play store and the Apple App Store
      %li After installing, set Signal as your default SMS application for ease of use
      %li Signal is also available for desktop as a Chrome app
